There fore please investigate the new type for this and incorporate the changes. As communicated by Indika we could use .DOCS support.

Summary: AARESAA-5485 PNL/ADL - Support meal with standard IATA codes
Description:
When meal details are displayed, in current implementation for Air Arabia, meal code is included in PNL/ADL with hard coded SPML SSR code. 
This needs to be changed to get the IATA code from the meal table.

When 0 charged meals are made available, system should include the selected meal IATA code in the PNL/ADL. In this case, there is no need to include meal code. 

When meals with charges in a reservation, instead hard coded SPML, IATA code to be taken from the meal table and then followed with meal code as of now.

Summary: Capture DOCO information to include it in PNL/ADL as SSR
Sub-Tasks: AARESAA-16205, AARESAA-16217, AARESAA-16533, AARESAA-16918
Description:
Summary: - Capture DOCO information on AccelAero to include it in PNL/ADL as SSR for bookings through XBE/IBE
Scope:
1. DOCO (VISA) information to be captured during create/modify bookings on XBE/IBE for all applicable flights.
2. Following fields for Visa to be captured on XBE/IBE for applicable flights:
2.1. Place of birth 
2.2. Travel document type
2.3. Visa document number
2.4. Visa document place of issue
2.5. Visa document issue date
2.6. Country/state for which visa is applicable

Refer details in the below snapshot for the format to generate the PNL with DOCO information.

3. APP parameter to be introduced to enable DOCO on AccelAero. 
Out of Scope: DOCO information capturing on API bookings not considered.

In PNL when there are passengers who has same last name, system will group them to one line with 46 characters. Rest of the passengers marking in next line. But in ADL the number of characters per line is 64. When sending ADL it is displaying passegers who are with same last name upto 64 characters with the DEL records. But in ADD record it displaying as PNL format. Then PNL and ADL passenger records format becomming mismatch and count getting mismatch.

EX:
In PNL
4RASHED/AESHAMR/EBRAHIMMR/MUBARAKMR/SUMAYAMR-A8
2RASHED/FATEMAMR/NADAMR-A8

In ADL DEL section
6RASHED/NADAMR/FATEMAMR/EBRAHIMMR/MUBARAKMR/AESHAMR/SUMAYAMR-A8

In ADL ADD section
4RASHED/AESHAMR/EBRAHIMMR/MUBARAKMR/SUMAYAMR-A8
2RASHED/FATEMAMR/NADAMR-A8

Sample PNL:
G90666
SHJ
21/04/2011

PNR : 22670537

Summary: AARESAA-26390 PNL/ADL : The Horizontel name sort issue
Description:
Steps: 
1) go to http://g9cmb2.isaaviations.com/xbe/private/showXBEMain.action 
2) Place a reservation with multiple passengers having same last-name with with different titles 

MRS AAA PERERA 
MS CCC PERERA 
MR DDD PERERA 
MRS BBB PERERA 
MISS AAB PERERA 
MASTER AAE PERERA 

3) Send the PNL 

Actual Result: 

system sorts the pax details Horizontally by the Title and not considering the alphabetical order as before 

current behavior 
ex: 7PERERA/DDDMR/BBBMRS/AAAMRS/CCCMS/AAEMSTR/ABAMSTR/ABBMISS-B8 


earlier the system sorted the names based on the alphabetical order 
6PERERA/AAAMRS/AABMISS/AAEMSTR/ABAMSTR/ABBMISS/BBBMRS-A8 


Expected Result: 

a) When we checked the PSCRM 34th edition its not mentioned to display the name in any of these sorting orders 

page : 823 28th Edition 2008 - Not sorting by Title 

b) 2.6.4.4 28th Edition 2008 page 805 , its not sorted based on alphabetical order 

c) In earlier the Air Arabia has sorted by Alphabetical (Horizontally ) order and not sure whether the new fix may cause a confusion 

d) we have asked from support team and they only knows the Previous behavior

Summary: QA TASK Capture DOCO information to include it in PNL/ADL as SSR
Sub-Tasks: AARESAA-16819, AARESAA-16825, AARESAA-16829, AARESAA-16854, AARESAA-16869, AARESAA-16883, AARESAA-16886, AARESAA-16888, AARESAA-16900, AARESAA-16902, AARESAA-16905, AARESAA-16907, AARESAA-16913, AARESAA-16915, AARESAA-16944
Description:
Summary: - Capture DOCO information on AccelAero to include it in PNL/ADL as SSR for bookings through XBE/IBE 
Scope: 
1. DOCO (VISA) information to be captured during create/modify bookings on XBE/IBE for all applicable flights. 
2. Following fields for Visa to be captured on XBE/IBE for applicable flights: 
2.1. Place of birth 
2.2. Travel document type 
2.3. Visa document number 
2.4. Visa document place of issue 
2.5. Visa document issue date 
2.6. Country/state for which visa is applicable 

Refer details in the below snapshot for the format to generate the PNL with DOCO information. 

3. APP parameter to be introduced to enable DOCO on AccelAero. 
Out of Scope: DOCO information capturing on API bookings not considered.

Summary: AARESAA-9437 ADL sending wrong for Cancel segment of Return booking
Description:
In the current Zest Production ADL send after cancel segment of return booking results in invalidating the both segments in DCS.

This same issue is also present for normal ADL as well.

Summary: Duplicate PNL/ADLs sending issue when multiple SITA/email addresses
Description:
In a scenario where multiple SITA/email addresses are configured for sending PNL/ADLs for specific airport, in some scenarios when a transmission failure occurs for a single SITA/email address, system fails to record PNL/ADL history, even though PNL/ADL is sent to other addresses. As history is not recorded, system generates duplicate PNL/ADL if there are no changes
in the flight and sent to SITA/email addresses which has already received the PNL/ADL with the same content.

Summary: AARESAA-5450 LCCDRYP2 - XBE/IBE/WS - PNL/ADL/Manifest/Reports - Pax details configuration changes to be handled
Description:
Pax details to capture should be made configurable per airline.
Pax details to capture configurations are to be maintained per pax category per pax type.

Implementation to cover XBE, IBE and Webservices pax details handling in create booking, modify pax basic info and view/edit pax additional info.

FOID capturing done separately to be eliminated and all the pax details are to be handled in uniform way.
DOB validations are continued to be kept in T_PAX_TYPE however all mandatory/optional/grouping configurations for all the pax details are to be maintained in separate configuration table.

Additional pax details are to be stored in separate table that forms 1:1 relationship with T_PNR_PASSENGER.

Reservation changes done under AARESAA-5580
Following changes are to be done and record status under this jira. 
1. Additional pax information in PNL/ADL 
2. Flight manifest - pax info and additional pax info 
3. Reports

Summary: AARESAA-4862 Duplicate Names in PNL
Description:
Have noticed Duplicate Names going on PNL for RT and 3O environments.


eg: RAK : RT303 10-Oct only 69Y booking in Manifest and PNL sends 103Y
Maroc : 3O437 8-Oct only 168Y bookings in Manifest and PNL sends 199Y

Still none of the airlines identified the issue and need to fix immediately. Going through code found two issues.

1. Wrong outer join condition on ReservationAuxilliaryDAOImpl.java line:2297 "OR pas.pax_cat_foid_id is null" causing records to be duplicated in Passport enabled Airlines. 
2. Pax_category_foid does not updated in t_pnr_passenger table when split reservation happens(Could be for other scenario's as well). As far as above issue 1 exist this will not be appear. But once above issue 1 fixed, PNL will be missing all those passengers and it will show less than actual passengers.

Summary: PNL, if sent manually before scheduled , and additional bookings made in between, the scheduled PNL is sent as a fresh PNL instead of re sending original , due to which PNR's are missed by DCS
Description:
PNL, if sent manually before scheduled , and additional bookings made in between, the scheduled PNL is sent as a fresh PNL instead of re sending original , due to which PNR's are missed by DCS 
Steps: 
Send a fresh PNL manually. tHis will gets accepted by DCS. 
Then make a booking 
Then trigger the scheduled PNL job 
The PNL gets sent as afresh PNL with the new booking made 
But DCS does not accept this PNL as already one is accepted 
Hence in future ADL's also this PNR will not go and is missed and unavailable on DCS 
Instead of sending fresh PNL in such case through scheduler, if already sent PNL exists it needs to just resend the PNL.

Summary: ADL message improvement
Description:
Current ADL messages are not complient with IATA standard. Therefore we system facing issues like AARESAA-3791 . Therefore following improvements need to be done on ADL's

- MultiPart Handling of ADL should not split one or part of the name elements. (IATA Manual, Section 1707b, Section 2.7)

- MultiPart Handling of ADL should repeat the header commands in case of splitting. (IATA Manual, Section 1708, Section 1.3)

Summary: AARESAA-15194 XBE - If reservation within baggage cut off time and outside reservation buffer time in XBE , no default baggage is assigned , due to which if ADL sent after reservation cut over , it fails
Description:
XBE - If reservation within baggage cut off time and outside reservation buffer time in XBE , no default baggage is assigned , due to which if ADL sent after reservation cut over , it fails
Eg :Say SHJ- BLR flight at 6:00 :p.m same day 
Then make a reservation with user who does not have privilege to book baggage in cut off time : SHUSSAIN 
The reservation should be made at 5:25 p.m , such that it is within baggage cut off time of 4 hrs , but > 30 mins of departure 
Then send ADL once reservation cut off time has passed i.e : 5:45 
Then ADL sending fails
This is because of no baggage mentioned in PNR
If from backend its updated as NOBAG in such a case, and then send ADL it goes through 
Hence in such case , by default NOBAG should have been assigned

column name : FOID_SSR_CODE
data type : VARCHAR2(4 BYTE)
nullable : No

constraint type : Foreign key

values : for the airports GOI,PVG,DUS,DEL value should be "DOCS" and for others "PSPT"

This change needs to be done only in Mahan DB.

Summary: QA task Activate past flights to take action on them
Sub-Tasks: AARESAA-15107, AARESAA-15109, AARESAA-15111, AARESAA-15112, AARESAA-15119, AARESAA-15127, AARESAA-15129, AARESAA-15142, AARESAA-15191, AARESAA-15278, AARESAA-15379, AARESAA-15380
Description:
QA task Activate past flights to take action on them
In some cases, flights get delayed in the airport(due to bad weather etc) at the last moment, but AccelAero flight info not get updated. In that case, AccelAero close the flight in the system. But in reality, airline needs to do some actions like reprotect passengers, transfer passengers to other flight, change the flight time in the system to new time etc. Also they may need to send ADL/PNL if they reschedule the flight. We need to allow privileged users to activate the closed flights.

"Possibility of past flight time and type changing and protecting PSGRS and possibility of doing normal and current actions on renewed flights, such as make a pnr/modifying a pnr/ sending pnl,adl /resending pnl,adl and......etc"

Not such a long date. At least 4 months is totally enough

If I understand you correctly, yes we are going to change some or all features of an old flight. But we always change the time of old flight to future

Summary: AARESAA-26501 W5 Scheduler node load average is abnormally high
Description:
W5 Scheduler node load average is abnormally high 

Consequences: 
-Interruptions and failures in scheduler processes [Badly Impacted on PNL/ADL transmission via sitatext] 

Findings from the Memory Dump 
- It is observed that higher number [3000] unusual collection of OutMessage.java objects were created in the memory in different threads 
reference DB table : MB_T_OUT_MESSAGE 

Synopsis 
- To identify the suspicious processes, added logs on scheduler node. 
- It is observed that, un-transmitted MB_T_OUT_MESSAGE records are getting picked every time and failing to update the status in MB_T_OUT_MESSAGE [Such accumulated number of DB entries are attached for the further investigations] 
==>Collection of OutMessage.java periodically created in memory {may be the current process is not getting completed in the next run of the same periodic process } and consumes resources undesirably. 

Suspected Processes: 
1] PNL/ADL transmission to sitatext

2] SSM/ASM transmission to UMAIR and MAB. 
Refer: 2_code_bloks_on_suspected_processes.png and 3_code_bloks_on_suspected_processes.png 

Justification/Proof 
Temporally marking the un-transmitted relevant records as transmitted in MB_T_OUT_MESSAGE for PNL/ADL and SSM/ASM, scheduler node came back to normal. [ Please refer the cpu-load graph] 
Note - Action on the such un-transmitted expired records [ which were marked as transmitted] needs be taken after discussing with leads.

Summary: CodeShare Implementation
Sub-Tasks: AARESAA-12551, AARESAA-19231, AARESAA-19239, AARESAA-19240, AARESAA-19241, AARESAA-19243, AARESAA-19259, AARESAA-19262, AARESAA-19263, AARESAA-19284, AARESAA-19355, AARESAA-19389, AARESAA-19471, AARESAA-19688, AARESAA-19706, AARESAA-19718, AARESAA-19737, AARESAA-19739, AARESAA-19740, AARESAA-19741, AARESAA-19742, AARESAA-19743, AARESAA-19744, AARESAA-19895, AARESAA-19952, AARESAA-20047, AARESAA-20074, AARESAA-20076, AARESAA-20118, AARESAA-20343, AARESAA-20344, AARESAA-20476, AARESAA-23379, AARESAA-23530, AARESAA-23533, AARESAA-23868, AARESAA-23869, AARESAA-23870, AARESAA-23917, AARESAA-23919, AARESAA-23997, AARESAA-24054, AARESAA-24335, AARESAA-24534, AARESAA-24657
Description:
Mainly this includes 2 sections. 

1. AccelAero as Operating Carrier (OC) 

* Codeshare(CS) airline can be configured in the system. 
* For AccelAero operating flights/schedules, CS flight numbers can be added. 
* AccelAero operating flights/schedules can be published as SSM/ASM messages to CS airline. If CS flight numbers are already mentioned in the flights/schedules, those CS flight numbers will be in the messages. Else only AccelAero flight numbers will be in the messages. 
* Once AccelAero flights/schedules published, AVS/NAVS messages started to send which contains the inventory details. 
* In GDS screen, there is a possibility of sending SSM/ASM for all AccelAero flights/schedules at once (SSM/ASM recap) to the CS airline or GDS. Then system starts to send AVS/NAVS for the published flights/schedules. Also AccelAero can send the SSIM file which contains flights that contains CS MC flight details. 
* CS airline will send the booking messages to AccelAero and system will process those messages and do requested operations( booking creation/modification etc) 
* If inventories are changed due to own airline operations in AccelAero, those will be notified to CS airline by AVS/NAVS messages. 
* There is an assumption that booking messages will contain only the flights which are shared with CS airline.(no validation has done to avoid avoid to make reservations for unpublished flights because all flights were supposed to publish in the codeshare agreement between W5 and UF. Also we are not tracking passive segments comes in the booking messages) 
* Etickets will be issued by MC and AccelAero will receive MC etickets by SSR TKNE messages. 
* PNRs which are booking by CS MC airline, those pnrs will be not allowed to modify through AccelAero.( we can enable it by configuration to send systematization messages which is not tested for codeshare project) 
* PNL/ADL will be send by OC with the MC eticket details and MC flight details. 
* Once AccelAero receives PFS/ETL, it will create and transmit a Marketing PFS/ETL to the MC. Also system will not allow to manual PFS/ETL processing for some pnrs/etl while that segment is booked by CS airline. 


2. AccelAero as Marketing Carrier (MC) 
* CS OC will send the SSM/ASM messages. AccelAero process those messages and will create flights/schedules based on that. 
* CS OC will send the NAVS messages. AccelAero process those messages and will allocate inventory for created CS flights/schedules. 
* AccelAero will not allow to change the inventory for those CS flights through AccelAero UI. 
* When reservations are done on these flights, booking messages will be sent to CS OC airline. Relevant modifications also will be sent. These booking messages will contain only flights which are operated by CS airline. Own airline flight segments will not be sent in these booking messages. 
* Eticket information will be sent in SSR TKNE messages. 
* For these flights, PNL/ADL will not be sent from AccelAero. 
* PFS/ETL will be sent by CS OC airline and AccelAero will process it same as other PFS/ETLs 

General Rules: 
(1) Onhold timelimit of OC will be applied for GDS/Codeshare bookings. 
(2) There is no standard way to send contact person names. So, first Pax name will be used as contact person name in OC side. Also this name will not be able to edit from MC side. 
(3) Usernote details in MC will not be synced to OC. 
(4) When we are configuring BCs for GDS/Codeshare, we need to publish only onhold allowed BCs. 
(5) Cant unpublish a single flight from published schedule. 
(6) GDS/Codeshare pnrs will not be served by connection fares. 
(7) Booking type ofGDS/Codeshare pnrs will be 'standard'. Not the 'charter'. 
(8)When Mahan publish a flight to GDS/CS, IATA aircraft model should have defined for the attached aircraft model. IATA aircraft model 
should be 3 letters which are defined in IATA SSIM manual. 
(9) When we publish a flight to GDS/CS, configured booking classes will be added to the Mahan(OC side) flight with 0 allocations. User can remove those allocation if required when there are no bookings. Even for such deleted BC flight, if user do the Aircraft model change, then again those configured booking classes will be added. 
(10) In Operating carrier(Mahan), when booking is searched from standard booking class, seat can be nested even from unpublished standard booking classes. 




IATA Manual reference - 

SSIM-2007.pdf 
SSM/ASM 
Chapter 4 — STANDARD SCHEDULES MESSAGE PROCEDURE [143] 
Page - 143 
Chapter 5 — AD HOC SCHEDULES MESSAGE PROCEDURE [209] 
Page - 209 

AIRIMP35th Edition.pdf 
AVS => CHAPTER 4 — AVAILABILITY STATUS MESSAGES [233] 

Page - 233 
PNL/ADL 
Reference Manual – PSCRM28 
Pages: 775, 790, 821 
PNL/ADL 1708 


PFS 
Reference Manual – PSCRM28 
Page: 887 
PFS – 1719 


ETL 
Reference Manual – PSCRM28 
Page: 909

Summary: QRTZ data issue
Description:
We have cleared AccelAero QRTZ data yesterday night due to limitation of the free space in QRTZ_DATA.
With this clearing task it removes already scheduled ADL triggers also and it will not start again even we start PNL/ADL scheduler at the same time.

Currently all the ADL triggers will schedule when PNL trigger schedules in qrtz table.Our PnlADLTxSchedular Trigger checking all the future flights after 24 hours and schedule PNL/ADL according to the configurations.

We have two options to avoid such situations in live,

1.We can check all the exiting scheduled triggers keep backup of them and clear the qrtz data - we will check this with shankar

2.We can change PNL/ADL scheduler behaviour to pick up all the future flights(within 1 day) and reschedule all the triggers which was cleared.

Summary: ETL-PFS - PRL for flight with 3 digit number
Description:
Attached the CR description. 

Overview:ETL/PFS/PRL for flight with 3 digit number by applying TTY address 
Existing Behaviour: 
Currently PFS/ETL/PRL is processed only for flights which have exact matching flight number as mentioned in the PNL/ADL sent from AccelAero.If the PFS/ETL/PRL from DCS sends different flight number then it’s not processed. 
Details of CR: 
Currently at certain instances there is mismatch between flight number for same flight in DCS and in AccelAero(CRS) 
To overcome this obstacle for PFS/ETL/PRL processing: 
1. PFS/ETL/PRL sent by DCS to AccelAero 
2. AccelAero to check: 
2.1. Flight number in PFS/ETL/PRL sent by DCS = Flight number in PNL/ADL sent by AccelAero 
2.2. If YES : 
2.2.1. PFS/ETL/PRL to be processed by AccelAero 
2.3. If NO: 
2.3.1. AccelAero to check if last three digits of Flight Number in PFS/ETL/PRL and last three digits of Flight Number in PNL/ADL is same. 
2.3.2. If last three digits of Flight Number match then check if first digit is Zero in the PFS/ETL/PRL sent by DCS. 
2.3.3. If yes, then remove the first zero of the flight number in PFS/ETL/PRL and process the PFS/ETL/PRL at AccelAero. 
Example: 
1. PNL/ADL for flights W5060, W5062, W5064 sent by AccelAero 
2. If DCS adds 0 to above flights it will be W50060, W50062, W550064. When the DCS sends PFS/ETL/PRL, it should be processed by AccelAero by removing first zero from flight number

Summary: AARESAA-9692 Stop Creating new coupon number to the inbound, when cancelling the outbound
Description: Let say there is a return booking THR/BND. Outbound etkt coupon 1, inbound coupon 2. When we cancel the outbound, system keeps the same etkt for the inbound. but make the inbound coupon as 1. Need to stop creating new coupon number to the inbound, when cancelling the outbound. Because, when we have already sent pnl for the inbound, when we cancel the outbound, coupon changes of the inbound will not send through ADL will will create some issues in PFS/ETL processing.

Summary: Stop ET generation for forced confirmed bookings
Sub-Tasks: AARESAA-21735, AARESAA-23053, AARESAA-23126
Description:
Stop ET generation for forced confirmed bookings 

Rules: 
*************** 
1.ETs will not be generated in following scenarios. 
1.1 create booking force confirm 
1.2 confirmed booking modification force confirm 
1.3 Add infant and reservation get force confirm 

2. On full payment to the reservation, ETs will be generated for all passengers. 
3. When reservation has credits to settle the new segment modification and not going to payment page, then system will generate ETs when segment route modifications 
4. Generate ETs when Add ancillaries or chargeable SSRs and pay. 
5. When some passengers get confirmed due to partial payments, new ETs will be generated only for those passengers because those passengers get split automatically by the system and create new confirmed reservation. 
6. When reservation get forced confirm status to confirmed status by doing a payment, new ETs will be generated to all passengers. 
7. In minus charge adjustment, ETs are generated only for the passengers who get confirmed due to no balance to pay. Only those confirmed passengers will be sent in PNL/ADL. 
8. Open RT date modifications are considered as Ond changes and generated ETs earlier even if there are no balance to pay. Same behavior will be maintained. 

Notes: 
* Check Reports related to ETs 
* When one pax has credits and one pax has due. Reservation is still force confirmed. 
* Check PNL/ADL

Summary: Adding SITA ADDRESS to the system
Description:
Current system behavior 
==================== 
Users are able to add the SITA ADDRESS to the airport. 

Business requirement 
================== 
Airarabia added new DCS system and added new SITA ADRRESS to SHJ hub to communicate with the new DCS system. They want to test one flight initially which is SHJ/KWI G9127. 
As there is no provision to be added the SITA ADDRESS to flight, System sends PNL/ADL for all flights from SHJ airport where it double the messages and impact the system performance. 

System impact 
============ 
Currently scheduler server is very unstable where it stuck time to time where it blocks the very important schedulers such as release onhold seats and release blocked seats.. etc 

Product development 
================== 
1. SYSTEM should give provision to define the sector for SITA ADDRESS and should give high priority to the SITA ADDRESS of the sector 
Eg SHJ/KWI ==> HDQWAG9 
2. Users should give provision to define the flight number for the SITA ADDRESS and should give high priority to the SITA ADDRESS of the flight 
Eg G9127 ==> HDQWAG9 

3. System should give same provision above point 1, 2 for adding email address 
1. SHJ/KWI ==> support@accelaero.com 
2. G9127 ==> support@accelaero.com

Summary: AARESAA-24406 Multiple times name change goes as DEL and ADD , when previously the PNR has never gone, due to which total count is incorrect
Description:

Steps: 
Make a booking with 2 TBA 
Then split the pax 
Then name change original PNR and send ADL 
Then name change new PNR 
Then again name change , with requote and keep as Force Confirmed (with balance to pay ) 
Then pay the balance 
Then send ADL 
It is sent as DEL record and then ADD 
Count does not get incremented due to this. --> NOT OK 
Eg PNR : 42835297 -SHJ 
Check attached ss issue7.jpg 
Previous ADL total count was 6 
This ADL has DEL and ADD and count remains 6 which is wrong 
Check manifest - Count is 7

Summary: MahanAir - Remove paper ticket usage
Sub-Tasks: AARESAA-12179
Description:
MahanAir not defining the correct aircraft capacity in the AccelAero. As an example, let say AirBus 310 capacity is 250. MahanAir define the capacity as 220 in the AccelAero, allowing to sell that 30 seats by goshow agents in the airport. To remove the paper ticket usage, you want that allow goshow agents to make reservations during cutoff time for those 30 seats. We have already provided a privilege to make reservations during cutoff time, but which consume inventory which is defined in the system (i.e 220), not the seats which are not defined in the system.

We can implement it like this. 'Make reservations during cufoff time' privilege should be assigned to GOSHOW agents only. Every flight should have Goshow booking class inventory allocations(high value like 100) and valid goshow fare should be defined in the system.(currently goshow inventory created in the time of PFS processing). Goshow booking class should not be a fixed booking class. Goshow fares should link only to those goshow agents in the airport. Goshow agents should be able to book only from goshow fares (for this we need to do some implementation, because currently agents will get public fares as well.) If goshow agents make bookings during cutoff time, they should be able to overbook the flight( skipping Inventory check should handle by the same privilege mentioned above). Goshow agents should have void privilege, then they can fully refund those amounts, when cancel such reservation.

************************************
Dear Kermani,

If the booking is done before send the last ADL, then that information will be in ADL. But if the booking is done after sending the last ADL, then those passengers will come as NOREC passengers in PFS.

Thanks & Regards,
Manoj

Summary: AARESAA-6765 Excess Baggage Booking ( Chargable/ FOC ) Optional Selection
Description:
Excess Baggage Booking ( Chargable/ FOC ) Optional Selection

1. Baggages to be added FOC.
2. A privilege user to change and override the baggage price amount if required.

08DEC11 IL=> NOTE

Also with this change I have changed the baggage selection mandatory flow which is related to RES_109 param. i.e if RES_109 enabled, then user should not be able remove baggage and default one should be automatically selected (default baggage should configure from the admin). if that param is disabled, user should be able to remove selected baggages and no need to have default baggages.

Earlier even though that app param was there, baggage selection hard coded to be mandatory.

Summary: AARESAA-5807 LCCDRYP2 - XBE/IBE/WS - Create booking - Pax details - Make it configurable per airline
Description:
Pax details to capture should be made configurable per airline.
Pax details to capture configurations are to be maintained per pax category per pax type.

Implementation to cover XBE, IBE and Webservices pax details handling in create booking, modify pax basic info and view/edit pax additional info.

FOID capturing done separately to be eliminated and all the pax details are to be handled in uniform way.
DOB validations are continued to be kept in T_PAX_TYPE however all mandatory/optional/grouping configurations for all the pax details are to be maintained in separate configuration table.

Additional pax details are to be stored in separate table that forms 1:1 relationship with T_PNR_PASSENGER.

Summary: AARESAA-5485 Airport Maintenance - Capture meal notification Parameters
Description:
Airport maintenance screen needs to be changed to capture following details. 

New flag to indicate if Meal notifications enabled for the airport
If enabled, following parameters to be specified
- Capture catering email in comma separated format (similar thing available in agent maintenance billing email id)
- Capture Meal Notification times in following format.
- Meal Notification start time (hh:mm before departure)
- Meal Notification frequency ( mins )
- Last Meal Notification time ( hh:mm before departure)

All times should be properly validated. Hours could be upto 999. Minutes has to be upto 59 only
Last meal notification time should not be more that start time

Summary: New Goshow process
Sub-Tasks: AARESAA-16343
Description:
Summary: New GO SHOW process which would make agents to make payment at the time of booking.
Scope of CR¬:
1. User can make reservations to any flight which is not in the cutoff time.
2. If the user has 'Allow create bookings after reaching XBE Res cut-off time' privilege, user can make reservations for the flights which are in cutoff time on any RBD and any fare which is accessible to that user. 
3. User should be able to make return reservations where outbound is in cutoff time and inbound is not in cutoff time. 
4. New privilege "Allow over bookings after reaching XBE Res cut-off time" to be introduced: 
4.1. If a user has this privilege, this user can overbook the flight which is already reached cutoff time. 
4.2. If the user does not have "Allow over bookings", the user can't overbook the other flights. 
5. Open return bookings should be possible.
6. New privilege "Allow Cancel Reservation after reaching XBE Res cut-off time" to be introduced: 
6.1. If a user has this privilege, this user can cancel a reservation which has a flight which is already reached cutoff time. (Currently buffer time cancel reservation only allow with the privilege "Allow Modifying Expired Reservations")
7. Currently system has a privilege for "Void Reservations". We can divide it to 2 like "Void Own reservations" and "Void Others reservations". "Void Own reservations" privilege will allow User to void their own reservations only. 
7.1. If we assign the "Void Own reservations" privilege to the airport users, they can void any reservations done by them if they match with the void conditions in the system. Not only the bookings done by them for the flights in cutoff time.
7.2. These users can void only before flight departure since these agents will not have "Allow Modifying Expired Reservation."
8. ADL timing in reservation cut off time to be maintained separately. 

Other Details:
• Void means cancel the full amount and it will come as credits in the PNR. Agents will have to do the refund manually.
• System will allow only Void reservations. Not the void segments. Therefore, any bookings done within the cut-off time for a flight and that booking include any future segments as well, then user should Void the reservation, which will cancel the future segment as well.
• The purpose of GOSHOW agents in the system is, when we processing goshow bookings in PFS, we debit that ticket amount to Goshow agents account. But with new solution, agent make the payment at the time of booking. Therefore, there is no relation with goshow agents in new solution.

---------------------------
Agreed following changes in email "Scope of New goshow process" on 30Jan2014
1. keep the existing "Void Reservations" privilege (which allows to void own and others) and introduce new privilege to "Void Own reservations only".
2. Remove GY1,GC1 feature permanently.

Summary: AARESAA-18124 Seat appears duplicate in Flight manifest when doing same flight modification
Description:
Steps : 

1) Make a booking for SHJ/BAH/-BAH/SHJ G9105-G9104 for 21/02-23/02 without flexi onhold 
2) Select seats for SHJ/BAH-BAH/SHJ as 1 A-1A 
3) Now modify BAH/SHJ to same date & flight with flexi 
4) Now select a new seat because seat selection is removed for BAH/SHJ , say 11 C 
5) Proceed with the payment & Force confirm 
6) View the Flight manifest for BAH/SHJ G9104 
As shown in screenshot (g9_seat_3) the seat selected for BAH/SHJ is removed 
As in the screenshot (g9_seat_6) the flight manifest now shows both seats are selected for BAH/SHJ 
REFER PNR :36727641

Summary: Allow access Web bookings - Privilege issue
Description:

Only after giving allow search any PNR, agents can access web bookings.

For normal agents and GSA agents, after giving "Allow access Web bookings" privilege, they should be able to search web bookings.

Summary: AARESAA-6765 Discount Facility
Description:
Let the users define a discount range in the master / fare rule level.

During the XBE fare quote level, privilege users are allowed to give discount up to the maximum range defined in the fare rule. This will be done by entering the discount percentage and getting the fare quote again. In the new fare quote, discounted fare and taxes (taxes or charges which are defined as percentage of fare will be calculated based on original fare not based on discounted fare)

Summary: AARESAA-5485 AirAdmin - Meal Maintenance - Support FOC charges, IATA Codes and Multiple class of services
Description:
Following changes are to be done

- Add selecting and saving of IATA SSR's for Meals - For meal SSR's, a new category would be added to SSR table and these needs to be displayed as a drop down.
If only 1 meal SSR code is enabled, it should be the default selected value. 
Mandatory selection.

- Adding facility of Class of Service for a meal - incase of a single COS airline, value should be defaulted and user need not select a value. This must be a mandatory selection. 

- Allowing to enter 0 charge meals - If application parameter is set to allow 0 meals, should allow to save with a 0 meal charge. 

Search and Grid display
- Include COS & IATA Meal code in search and in the grid
